  "prompt": "How is winter in Houston?",
  "response": "Winters in Houston are generally mild compared to many other parts of the United States. Here are some key characteristics:\n\n1. Temperature\n- Average winter temperatures range from 40-60\u00b0F (4-15\u00b0C)\n- Rarely drops below freezing\n- Occasional cold fronts can bring short periods of colder weather\n\n2. Precipitation\n- Winter can be relatively wet\n- Some rain and occasional light freezing conditions\n- Snow is extremely rare, happening only once every few years\n\n3. General conditions\n- Generally comfortable and short winter season\n- Much milder than northern U.S. regions\n- Light jackets or sweaters are usually sufficient\n- Can be unpredictable with sudden temperature changes\n\n4. Outdoor activities\n- Most outdoor activities remain possible\n- Good time for gardening and outdoor recreation\n- Less humid than summer months\n\n5. Potential weather events\n- Occasional frost\n- Rare ice storms\n- Possibility of brief cold snaps\n\nOverall, Houston's winters are short, mild, and generally pleasant, with minimal risk of severe winter weather.",
